{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd302197-f903-434f-b732-44510a0130f2","content":"In .NET 10 MAUI, the iOS-specific `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` attached property was replaced with a **cross-platform** `SafeAreaRegions` property on `Page`.\n\n**Old (.NET 9):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\">\n```\n\n**New (.NET 10):**\n```xml\n<ContentPage SafeAreaRegions=\"All\">\n```\n\nYou can also target specific edges with the flags enum:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Top + Bottom only -->\n<ContentPage SafeAreaRegions=\"Top,Bottom\">\n```\n\nAvailable values: `None`, `Top`, `Bottom`, `Left`, `Right`, `All`.\n\nSince it's now a cross-platform property, you can also drop the `xmlns:ios` namespace declaration if `UseSafeArea` was the only thing using it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bac64c44-8917-481c-b181-a4776f2f36f8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI migration issue from .NET 9 to .NET 10 regarding safe area handling on iOS. This is a known breaking change in .NET 10 MAUI.\n\nIn .NET 10, the `UseSafeArea` attached property was removed/changed. The new approach uses padding-based safe area insets or the new `SafeAreaRegions` property.\n\nLet me recall what I know:\n\nIn .NET 10 MAUI, the `ios:Page.UseSafeArea` property was replaced. The new approach is to use the `Page.SafeAreaRegions` property which is cross-platform (not iOS-specific anymore).\n\n\nThe replacement uses a `SafeAreaRegions` property that accepts values like `All`, `Top`, `Bottom`, `Left`, `Right`, or `None` to control which areas of the page respect safe area insets. This is now a cross-platform API rather than iOS-specific, so you'd set it directly on the `ContentPage` without the iOS namespace prefix. The `SafeAreaRegions` property is a cross-platform replacement that accepts a flags enum with options like `None`, `Top`, `Bottom`, `Left`, `Right`, and `All`, eliminating the need for iOS-specific markup in the XAML namespace.","outputTokens":1009,"requestId":"3C33:30490E:DC2004:11209BC:6A012CED"},"id":"e2e6bdb0-46ab-4ac8-b9e1-828700c8b3bf","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:12:30.836Z","parentId":"a6dc7fb4-d771-4ca3-97e3-103c09f8c432"}
